Step into a slice of Ghana right in the heart of London! I visited the legendary Nsawam Market African Store in Mitcham (282 London Rd, CR4 3NB), and it felt like being transported straight to the bustling markets of Accra. From fresh kenkey, waakye leaves, and authentic Ghanaian spices to rare African snacks you won’t find anywhere else—this place is a cultural goldmine! Watch till the end for a surprise taste test that will blow your mind. Don't worry if it's a new experience, they're super helpful and ready to answer any questions. You can't go wrong with any of these dishes. Anything with fufu, caramelized plantains, jollof rice, and the Zongo Street Wakye platter are some of my favorites! PS.
